main event: A witness observed a rectangular silver-white object in the sky for 25 minutes before it dimmed and disappeared behind a cloud bank.
interesting points: The sighting occurred on June 10, 1960, at 10:30 PM in Los Angeles, California., The object remained stationary for the entire 25 minutes., The witness was identified as J.M. Simmons., The report indicates there were no photographs taken during the incident., The object was highly reflective in color, described as silver-white.
